\id GEN - Test Bible
\h Genesis
\toc1 Genesis
\toc2 Genesis
\toc3 Gen
\mt Genesis
\c 1
\p
\v 1 In the beginning God created the heavens and the earth.
\v 2 The earth was formless and empty, and darkness covered the deep waters. And the Spirit of God was hovering over the surface of the waters.
\v 3 Then God said, "Let there be light," and there was light.
\c 2
\p
\v 1 So the creation of the heavens and the earth and everything in them was completed.
\v 2 On the seventh day God had finished his work of creation, so he rested from all his work.
\v 3 And God blessed the seventh day and declared it holy, because it was the day when he rested from all his work of creation.
